        "text": "Actually, circling back to this now:\n\nCan we leverage this existing scala code to piece together a script that third-party node operators can run against their nodes for onboarding? Or do we need to rewrite this in a python\/shell script?\n\nIt would be cool if I could just copy the relevant bits to a new `sc` file, wrap it in a shell script that takes a remote-connect URL, and could download the necessary signed messages we need to collect. Is this doable\/reasonable?\n\nAnd related to this, it seems to me that we need multiple rounds of distribute-collect for the whole flow:\n• nodes create namespaces (or is this implicit by them running a node? can we use those existing keys\/namespaces?)\n• _collect_ namespaces to create the `DecentralizedNamespaceDefiniton` \n• _distribute_ that, so that\n• nodes can set up `party_to_key_mappings`...\n• _distribute_ messages to be signed\n• _collect_ those, submit\nThanks!",
